Endpoint	HTTP Method	Description							
/gateway/routes	GET	Returns a list of all defined routes in the gateway.							
/gateway/routes/{id}	GET	Returns information about a single, specific route.							
/gateway/routes/{id}	POST	Adds a new route to the gateway dynamically.							
/gateway/routes/{id}	DELETE	Deletes an existing route dynamically.							
/gateway/globalfilters	GET	Returns a list of all applied global filters.							
/gateway/routefilters	GET	Returns a list of all GatewayFilter factories applied to routes.							
/gateway/refresh	POST	Clears the routes cache. Useful if you've dynamically changed routing rules and need them to take effect immediately.							